THE Presidency has confirmed that American President Donald Trump has asked for a teleconference with President Jacob Zuma. The Presidency said in a Twitter post that the conversation is expected to take place this afternoon.It will be the first time the two presidents speak since Trump was inaugurated in January.Zuma had sent a congratulatory message to Trump after he won elections in November and said he looked forward to building on the relations that exist between the countries, including promoting peace and security, especially on the African continent. It is still unclear if Trump's administration would prioritise US-Africa relations.&nbsp;http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/trump-asks-to-speak-to-jacob-zuma-20170213